1. github create a repository xx
2. install github desktop
3. github desktop file - new respository,  
 name: My_Website (or whatever the folder name of backup website)
 path: /media/Backup/ (or path to the backup website upper 1 leve)
4. click create respository
5. repository - push  use pg1 as repository name if you want

6. in github, click on the repository, then "setting"
7. change it to public if not
8. under github pages - source, change to master
9. check under github pages, now you will see "your site is published at https://xxx.io/respository name

